gement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-ai-jobs-career-no-college-degree-deathcore-singer-skills-2025-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I've%20managed%20hundreds%20of%20employees.%20Here%20are%20the%20top%205%20things%20people%20do%20wrong%20when%20asking%20for%20promotions%20or%20raises%20%26amp%3Bmdash%3B%20and%20what%20to%20do%20instead.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223648%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22headshot%20of%20a%20woman%20in%20a%20brown%20dress%20and%20a%20leather%20jacket%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68b8697da17a8c5b4053ee40%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222736%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAndrea%20Wasserman.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Andrea%20Wasserman%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EExecutive%20coach%20Andrea%20Wasserman%20says%20timing%20is%20one%20of%20the%20most%20crucial%20parts%20of%20a%20promotion%20decision.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ERaises%20are%20business%20decisions%2C%20not%20gifts%2C%20and%20understanding%20the%20context%20around%20you%20is%20key%20to%20success.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBuild%20credibility%20and%20align%20with%20business%20needs%20to%20improve%20your%20chances%20of%20career%20advancement.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20course%20of%20my%20career%20at%20companies%20like%20Nordstrom%2C%20Verizon%2C%20and%20Yahoo%2C%20I've%20hired%2C%20developed%2C%20and%20evaluated%20hundreds%20of%20employees.%20Many%20of%20them%20were%20smart%2C%20capable%2C%20and%20ambitious.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-pitch-change-in-role-to-your-manager-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EThey%20wanted%20promotions%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20they%20got%20them%20%E2%80%94%20but%20I've%20also%20turned%20down%20many%20requests.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20think%20the%20group%20that%20got%20their%20requests%20granted%20was%20innately%20more%20talented%20or%20harder%20working%20than%20the%20group%20that%20didn't%2C%20think%20again.%20The%20truth%20is%20that%2C%20most%20of%20the%20time%2C%20the%20request%20itself%20wasn't%20the%20problem.%20The%20candidate%20wasn't%20even%20the%20problem.%20It%20was%20the%20%3Cem%3Etiming%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20made%20the%20difference.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPromotions%20and%20pay%20raises%20are%20business%20decisions%2C%20not%20gifts.%20This%20means%20that%20even%20the%20strongest%20performers%20will%20hear%20%26quot%3Bnot%20now%26quot%3B%20if%20they%20ignore%20the%20situations%20that%20surround%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20five%20of%20the%20most%20common%20timing%20missteps%20I've%20seen%2C%20and%20what%20I%20wish%20more%20rising%20leaders%20would%20do%20differently.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2269a3a1b4-c581-46a5-b013-d95eafc2a2cb%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20You%20just%20got%20promoted%2C%20and%20you're%20already%20asking%20for%20more%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20surprisingly%20common.%20Someone%20gets%20promoted%20in%20January%20and%2C%20by%20April%2C%20they're%20asking%20for%20another%20raise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20once%20had%20a%20high%20performer%20who%20was%20promoted%20to%20senior%20manager%20after%20a%20solid%20year.%20Less%20than%2090%20days%20later%2C%20she%20sent%20me%20a%20proposal%20for%20another%20title%20change%20%E2%80%94%20accompanied%20by%20comp%20benchmarks%20and%20a%20list%20of%20expanded%20responsibilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20%3Cem%3Ewas%3C%2Fem%3E%20doing%20more%2C%20but%20she%20hadn't%20been%20in%20the%20role%20long%20enough%20to%20demonstrate%20success%20at%20that%20level%2C%20and%20she%20lacked%20the%20self-awareness%20that%20no%20one%20should%20ask%20for%20more%20every%20quarter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2231cbb02e-6f73-49ce-8763-04748a7a1bae%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20to%20do%20instead%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EKeep%20a%20record%20of%20what's%20changed.%20If%20your%20role%20evolves%20quickly%2C%20talk%20about%20that%20during%20check-ins%20with%20your%20manager.%20Understand%20your%20career%20path%20and%20the%20next%20opportunity%20for%20growth.%20Then%2C%20give%20the%20business%20time%20to%20see%20your%20impact%20before%20you%20ask%20to%20level%20up%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2281158ef0-5cf7-47df-b610-b9e9119ebae9%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20You%20bring%20it%20up%20in%20your%20first%20few%20meetings%20with%20a%20new%20manager%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20natural%20to%20want%20to%20impress%20a%20new%20boss.%20I've%20seen%20people%20use%20early%201%3A1s%20to%20talk%20about%20their%20career%20goals.%20This%20makes%20sense%20%E2%80%94%20to%20an%20extent.%20And%20it's%20fine%20to%20let%20your%20new%20manager%20know%20if%20you%20had%20conversations%20with%20your%20old%20manager%20about%20your%20path%20to%20a%20promotion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20when%20it%20turns%20into%20%26quot%3BWhat%20would%20it%20take%20for%20me%20to%20get%20promoted%20this%20year%3F%26quot%3B%20before%20the%20manager%20even%20understands%20your%20role%20(and%20hers!)%2C%20it%20can%20create%20the%20perception%20that%20you're%20only%20thinking%20about%20yourself.%20It's%20like%20walking%20into%20a%20room%20you've%20never%20been%20in%20before%20and%20immediately%20asking%20to%20rearrange%20the%20furniture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b0f4db90-7028-4bdc-8672-53021c37135d%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20to%20do%20instead%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EStart%20by%20understanding%20how%20your%20new%20manager%20defines%20success%20and%20taking%20an%20interest%20in%20her%20priorities%20and%20challenges.%20Ask%20smart%20questions%2C%20then%20deliver%2C%20and%20deliver%20consistently.%20You%20can%20talk%20about%20growth%20and%20next%20steps%20once%20you've%20built%20trust%20and%20credibility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22306f2678-b69d-4f31-a13a-e542f4edc25e%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20The%20team%20is%20off-track%2C%20or%20the%20business%20is%20under%20pressure%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20the%20hardest%20%26quot%3Bno%26quot%3B%20answers%20I've%20had%20to%20give%20were%20to%20employees%20who%20were%20deserving%20but%20seemed%20oblivious%20to%20what%20was%20going%20on%20around%20them.%20Even%20if%20you%20think%20you've%20done%20everything%20right%2C%20asking%20for%20more%20when%20the%20broader%20context%20is%20shaky%20can%20hurt%20your%20chances.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20had%20employees%20come%20to%20me%20during%20expense%20freezes%2C%20department%20restructures%2C%20or%20right%20after%20we%20missed%20our%20numbers%2C%20sometimes%20with%20very%20strong%20cases%20for%20advancement.%20In%20those%20moments%2C%20the%20ask%20just%20wasn't%20feasible%20for%20the%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22097da76e-5a82-4795-94b2-c7851a1e5a2b%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20to%20do%20instead%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EMake%20yourself%20even%20more%20valuable%20by%20showing%20that%20you%20can%20lead%20patiently%20through%20uncertainty.%20Be%20the%20person%20who%20brings%20stability%20when%20others%20are%20scrambling.%20Once%20the%20business%20starts%20to%20recover%20%E2%80%94%20and%20you've%20played%20a%20visible%20role%20in%20that%20%E2%80%94%20you'll%20be%20in%20a%20much%20stronger%20position%20to%20ask%20for%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a4208b6e-c24c-4240-998c-87868794b89f%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20You%20missed%20a%20milestone%20or%20received%20feedback%20you%20haven't%20yet%20incorporated%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20happens%20when%20someone%20moves%20too%20quickly%20after%20a%20mistake%20or%20learning%20opportunity.%20Maybe%20a%20key%20project%20didn't%20land%2C%20or%20they%20got%20feedback%20about%20how%20they%20lead%20meetings%2C%20and%20they%20haven't%20yet%20corrected%20for%20it.%20Then%2C%20a%20few%20weeks%20later%2C%20they're%20asking%20for%20a%20promotion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20their%20overall%20track%20record%20is%20strong%2C%20the%20timing%20is%20off.%20Leaders%20want%20to%20see%20that%20you%20can%20take%20input%2C%20apply%20it%2C%20and%20grow%20from%20it.%20If%20you%20haven't%20closed%20the%20loop%20on%20feedback%2C%20asking%20for%20more%20shows%20a%20lack%20of%20accountability%20and%20self-awareness.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20once%20had%20a%20direct%20report%20who%20delivered%20great%20work%20but%20struggled%20with%20cross-functional%20influence%20and%20managing%20senior%20leaders.%20We%20talked%20about%20it%20openly%2C%20and%20he%20was%20aware%20and%20committed%20to%20improving.%20Two%20weeks%20later%2C%20he%20asked%20if%20he%20was%20in%20line%20for%20a%20promotion%20that%20quarter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20too%20soon.%20He%20hadn't%20had%20time%20to%20show%20progress%20yet%2C%20and%20asking%20so%20soon%20after%20our%20conversation%20made%20it%20seem%20like%20he%20didn't%20understand%20the%20gravity%20of%20the%20feedback.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22cce2a3f0-b422-4a99-aea3-b135a0730cde%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20to%20do%20instead%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ESlow%20down%2C%20and%20shore%20up%20any%20doubts%20about%20your%20potential.%20When%20you%20hear%20feedback%2C%20don't%20just%20acknowledge%20it%20%E2%80%94%20change%20something.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20when%20you%20make%20the%20ask%2C%20it%20will%20be%20even%20stronger%20because%20your%20coachability%20and%20growth%20will%20become%20part%20of%20the%20case%20for%20advancement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a11cca4d-d69d-4a80-a3d9-0b3120568abd%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E5.%20You%20waited%20too%20long%20to%20bring%20it%20up%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20mistake%20is%20almost%20as%20common%20and%20equally%20costly%20as%20the%20others.%20Every%20once%20in%20a%20while%2C%20someone%20has%20come%20to%20me%20unexpectedly%20and%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BI'm%20ready%20for%20the%20next%20level.%26quot%3B%20If%20we%20hadn't%20been%20talking%20about%20growth%2C%20readiness%2C%20or%20performance%20over%20time%2C%20it%20could%20be%20challenging%20to%20make%20it%20happen%20quickly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBig%20asks%20shouldn't%20come%20out%20of%20nowhere.%20They%20require%20a%20track%20record%20with%20a%20narrative%2C%20relationships%2C%20and%20often%20a%20process.%20Depending%20on%20other%20career%20path%20timelines%20you've%20observed%2C%20your%20own%20performance%2C%20and%20the%20standard%20cycle%20of%20mid-year%20and%20year-end%20performance%20conversations%2C%20you%20might%20start%20talking%20about%20your%20career%20goals%20once%20you've%20been%20in%20your%20role%20for%206-12%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224793357c-f9e5-45dc-a609-309106352871%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20to%20do%20instead%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EMake%20career%20growth%20part%20of%20the%20regular%20conversation.%20Use%201%3A1s%20with%20your%20manager%20or%20HR%20to%20ask%20what%20overdelivering%20looks%20like.%20Get%20clarity%20on%20what's%20expected%20at%20the%20next%20level.%20That%20way%2C%20when%20you're%20ready%20to%20make%20a%20formal%20ask%2C%20your%20manager's%20already%20on%20the%20same%20page.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229e77d2ac-b82c-4257-9adf-22477cdd11ae%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt's%20not%20just%20about%20how%20well%20you%20ask%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20about%20when%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20no%20perfect%20time%20to%20ask%20for%20a%20raise%20or%20a%20promotion.%20Yet%2C%20there%20are%20wrong%20times%20and%20there%20%3Cem%3Eis%3C%2Fem%3E%20a%20smart%20time.%20It's%20usually%20after%20you've%20shown%20clear%20results%2C%20earned%20credibility%2C%20and%20positioned%20yourself%20inside%20the%20broader%20business%20picture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20preparing%20to%20make%20a%20case%2C%20put%20yourself%20in%20your%20manager's%20shoes%2C%20evaluate%20what's%20happening%20across%20the%20team%20or%20company%2C%20and%20ask%20yourself%2C%20%26quot%3BWill%20this%20timing%20make%20it%20easier%20or%20harder%20for%20me%20to%20get%20a%20'yes'%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftop-5-reasons-employees-denied-raises-promotions-2025-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1756976701000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68b8697da17a8c5b4053ee40%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftop-5-reasons-employees-denied-raises-promotions-2025-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Andrea%20Wasserman%20hired%2C%20developed%2C%20and%20evaluated%20hundreds%20of%20employees%20during%20her%20corporate%20career.%20She%20denied%20promotions%20for%20a%20few%20common%20reasons.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Andrea%20Wasserman)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A7%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftop-5-reasons-employees-denied-raises-promotions-2025-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Instagram%20(finally)%20has%20an%20iPad%20app%2C%20and%20it's%20like%20the%20Cadillac%20of%20doomscrolling%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221435%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22instagram%20for%20ipad%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68b8b3d0f9db348adc0ac86b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22807%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFinally%2C%20there's%20an%20iPad%20version%20of%20Instagram%3Cp%3EMeta%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finstagram%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EInstagram%3C%2Fa%3E%20finally%20made%20an%20iPad%20app.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt%20opens%20directly%20onto%20Reels%2C%20which%20suggests%20Meta%20knows%20you%20just%20want%20to%20watch%20videos%20on%20there.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EFinally%2C%20a%20way%20to%20brain-rot%20myself%20completely%20on%20my%20couch.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20long%20last%2C%20the%20white%20whale%20of%20iOS%20has%20been%20harpooned%3A%20Instagram%20finally%20made%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fabout.instagram.com%2Fblog%2Fannouncements%2Finstagram-for-ipad%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eapp%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20iPad.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShockingly%2C%20there%20had%20never%20been%20a%20true%20iPad%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finstagram-trying-to-be-more-social-map-friends-reposts-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EInstagram%3C%2Fa%3E%20app%20%E2%80%94%20you%20could%20download%20the%20regular%20Instagram%20mobile%20app%20and%20use%20it%20on%20an%20iPad%2C%20but%20it%20was%20a%20uniquely%20crummy%20experience%20%E2%80%94%20you%20could%20use%20it%20with%20a%20phone-sized%20display%20or%20zoomed%20out%2C%20and%20the%20whole%20thing%20was%20clunky%20and%20sad.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20there's%20a%20new%20iPad%20version%2C%20nearly%2015%20years%20after%20Instagram%20first%20launched.%20(The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fapple-ipad-vs-ipad-air%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EiPad%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20also%20launched%20in%202010%2C%20just%20barely%20predates%20Instagram.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20tried%20it%20out%20on%20my%20iPad%20(which%2C%20honestly%2C%20I%20don't%20use%20all%20that%20much%20other%20than%20occasionally%20for%20scrolling%20on%20the%20couch%20when%20I%20leave%20my%20phone%20in%20the%20other%20room)%2C%20and%20I%20have%20to%20say%3A%20This%20is%20the%20%3Cem%3ECadillac%3C%2Fem%3E%20of%20doomscrolling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20biggest%20difference%20the%20iPad%20app%20has%20from%20the%20phone%20version%20is%20that%20it%20always%20opens%20onto%20the%20Reels%20tab.%20No%20more%20pretense%20that%20you%20might%20be%20hoping%20to%20see%20%26quot%3Bphotos%26quot%3B%20from%20your%20%26quot%3Bfriends%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20main%20feed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20you'll%20see%20Stories%20at%20the%20top%2C%20should%20you%20choose%20to%20interact%20with%20those%20plebes%20you%20know%20in%20real%20life%20who%20cling%20to%20the%20sad%20concept%20of%20posting%20photos%20and%20videos%20from%20their%20real%20life%20to%20share%20with%20their%20close%20friends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221620%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Instagram's%20ipad%20app%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68b89bca32af4d666ef73007%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221620%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFinally%2C%20doomscrolling%20on%20Reels%20from%20the%20couch%20is%20a%20dream.%3Cp%3EMeta%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20I%20like%20best%20about%20the%20experience%20is%20that%20the%20sound%20on%20the%20first%20video%20you%20see%20is%20%3Cem%3Eoff%3C%2Fem%3E%20by%20default.%20But%20instead%20of%20having%20to%20tap%20the%20%F0%9F%94%8A%20icon%20in%20the%20corner%20of%20the%20frame%2C%20you%20simply%20scroll%20down%20slightly%2C%20and%20the%20sound%20starts%20playing.%20This%20saves%20you%20the%20highly%20unpleasant%20experience%20of%20opening%20an%20app%20and%20having%20sound%20start%20playing%20right%20away%2C%20and%20it's%20also%20more%20intuitive%20to%20just%20slightly%20scroll%20down%20than%20to%20hunt%20and%20tap%20for%20a%20sound%20on%2Foff%20icon.%20Great!%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20does%20it%20mean%20that%20Instagram's%20iPad%20app%20is%20so%20Reels-centric%3F%20A%20more%20video-first%20approach%20makes%20sense%20with%20Reels%20and%20iPads.%20Since%20iPads%20are%20popular%20for%20watching%20video%20content%20%E2%80%94%20YouTube%20or%20Netflix%20%E2%80%94%20why%20not%20sit%20back%20and%20watch%20some%20Reels%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstagram's%20official%20blog%20post%20says%3A%20%26quot%3BWith%20Instagram%20for%20iPad%2C%20we've%20redesigned%20the%20experience%20to%20reflect%20how%20people%20use%20bigger%20screens%20today%20%E2%80%94%20for%20lean%20back%20entertainment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBuddy%2C%20you%20don't%20have%20to%20tell%20me%20twice%20to%20lean%20back%20and%20stare%20at%20a%20screen%20until%20I%20feel%20numb%20inside!%20Thanks%2C%20Meta!%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20t