ever%20been%20a%20more%20uneasy%20time%20to%20commit%20to%20a%20degree%20than%20right%20now%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20class%20of%202029%20is%20on%20edge.%20Today's%2018-year-olds%20spent%20middle%20school%20locked%20down%20in%20a%20pandemic.%20They've%20grown%20up%20more%20online%20and%20socially%20isolated%20than%20past%20generations%2C%20and%20in%20the%20Healthy%20Minds%20Study%2C%20a%20survey%20conducted%20by%20a%20consortium%20of%20universities%2C%20more%20than%2030%25%20of%20students%20report%20feeling%20depressed%20and%2For%20anxious.%20The%20campuses%20they've%20just%20arrived%20at%20are%20entrenched%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flist-of-universities-targeted-by-trump-administration-doge-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eculture%20war%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20the%20Trump%20administration%20has%20cut%20research%20budgets%20or%20pulled%20funding%20to%20enforce%20restrictions%20on%20student%20protests%20and%20free%20speech.%20International%20students%20face%20added%20obstacles%20to%20getting%20visas%2C%20and%20their%20numbers%20may%20plummet%20this%20fall.%20Tuition%20and%20fees%20at%20some%20colleges%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20have%20begun%20to%20surpass%20%24100%2C000%20a%20year.%20The%20average%20Gen%20Zer%20is%20carrying%20%2423%2C000%20in%20student%20debt%2C%20Experian%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20the%20dream%20jobs%20these%20colleges%20are%20preparing%20them%20for%2C%20many%20are%20wondering%20how%20much%20longer%20they'll%20even%20exist%2C%20as%20companies%20look%20to%20embrace%20generative%20AI.%20And%20what%2C%20exactly%2C%20should%20%3Cem%3Ethey%20%3C%2Fem%3Ebe%20doing%20with%20AI%20themselves%3F%20The%20most%20native%20GenAI%20users%20yet%20have%20been%20caught%20between%20admonishments%20that%20the%20world%20will%20leave%20them%20behind%20if%20they%20don't%20master%20the%20ability%20to%20prompt%20ChatGPT%20and%20the%20risk%20of%20getting%20caught%20cheating%20on%20their%20assignments%20if%20they%20rely%20on%20the%20chatbot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENo%20wonder%20young%20Americans%20are%20increasingly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-college-university-war-get-rich-quick-schemes-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eskeptical%20that%20college%20is%20worth%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20time%20and%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmid%20all%20this%20uncertainty%2C%20colleges%20themselves%20are%20feeling%20their%20way%20through%20their%20own%20identity%20crises.%20The%20US%20college%20system%20is%20far%20from%20perfect%20today.%20It%20can%20be%20inefficient%20and%20full%20of%20bloated%20costs.%20Schools%20must%20balance%20appealing%20to%20employers%20by%20giving%20students%20workplace-ready%20hard%20skills%20while%20also%20providing%20chances%20for%20young%20people%20to%20stumble%20and%20become%20autonomous%20and%20resilient%20critical%20thinkers%20and%20collaborators.%20Those%20soft%20skills%20are%20the%20type%20that%20correlate%20to%20higher%20career%20success%2C%20especially%20as%20AI%20assumes%20more%20entry-level%20tasks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20to%20revolutionize%20and%20reimagine%20higher%20education%20in%20ways%20that%20connect%20curriculum%20to%20career%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Lynn%20Pasquerella%2C%20the%20president%20of%20the%20Association%20of%20American%20Colleges%20and%20Universities.%20That%20means%20making%20students%20more%20%26quot%3Badaptable%20and%20flexible%26quot%3B%20to%20rapid%20change%2C%20she%20says%2C%20but%20colleges%20must%20be%20better%20incorporating%20internships%20or%20programs%20that%20connect%20students%20to%20their%20local%20communities%20to%20gain%20work%20experience%20and%20that%20real-world%20perspective.%20%26quot%3BAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20we%20have%20to%20take%20into%20account%20the%20fact%20that%20increasingly%2C%20students%20want%20more%20than%20just%20getting%20a%20job.%20They%20want%20lives%20of%20meaning%20and%20purpose.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20idyllic%20college%20campus%20steeped%20in%20tradition%20is%20changing.%20Like%20many%20students%2C%20it%20just%20doesn't%20know%20what%20it%20wants%20to%20be%20yet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EYoung%20people%20are%20inundated%20with%20messages%20that%20the%20value%20of%20a%20college%20degree%20is%20drying%20up%20and%20that%20lucrative%20alternatives%20abound.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpalantir-launches-anti-college-internship-for-high-school-grads-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPalantir%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20offering%20fellowships%20to%20high%20schoolers%20who%20want%20to%20%26quot%3Bskip%20the%20indoctrination%26quot%3B%20of%20college%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-tech-founders-skipping-college-new-dropping-out-palantir-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESilicon%20Valley%20still%20loves%20the%20young%20founder%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20leaves%20the%20dorm%20in%20the%20dust.%20Gen%20Z%20values%20both%20autonomy%20and%20wealth%2C%20and%20there%20are%20legions%20of%20young%20TikTok%20and%20Instagram%20influencers%20showcasing%20how%20to%20achieve%20both%20without%20a%20degree%20%E2%80%94%20as%20Airbnb%20hosts%2C%20realtors%2C%20drop%20shippers%2C%20video%20game%20streamers%2C%20plumbers%2C%20OnlyFans%20influencers%2C%20and%20sales%20course%20gurus.%20Sam%20Altman%2C%20himself%20a%20Stanford%20dropout%2C%20said%20on%20a%20podcast%20in%20July%20that%20college%20was%20%26quot%3Bnot%20working%20great%20for%20most%20people%26quot%3B%20but%20that%20%26quot%3Bif%20you%20fast-forward%2018%20years%2C%20it's%20going%20to%20look%20like%20a%20very%2C%20very%20different%20thing%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20AI%20changes%20the%20demands%20of%20the%20education%20system.%20A%20new%20study%20from%20the%20Stanford%20Digital%20Economy%20Lab%20found%20that%20since%20AI%20adoption%20became%20commonplace%2C%20employment%20rates%20among%20workers%20ages%2022%20to%2025%20dropped%20a%20relative%2013%25%20in%20roles%20highly%20exposed%20to%20AI%2C%20like%20software%20development%20and%20customer%20service.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcharts-gen-z-college-grads-job-market-hiring-unemployment-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eperks%20of%20earning%20a%20degree%3C%2Fa%3E%20may%20feel%20elusive%20to%20some%20recent%20grads%20and%20students%2C%20a%20degree%20remains%20the%20most%20tried%20and%20true%20way%20to%20build%20wealth%20over%20time.%20%26quot%3BThe%20level%20of%20uncertainty%20and%20risk%20is%20as%20high%20as%20it's%20ever%20been%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20understanding%20what%20the%20value%20proposition%20of%20pursuing%20a%20degree%20is%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Zack%20Mabel%2C%20the%20director%20of%20research%20at%20the%20Georgetown%20University%20Center%20on%20Education%20and%20the%20Workforce.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20matters%20is%2C%20what's%20a%20young%20person's%20fallback%20option%20if%20they%20don't%20go%20to%20college%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGen%20Z%20college%20graduates%20in%202024%20brought%20home%20a%20median%20salary%20of%20%2460%2C000%2C%20based%20on%20data%20from%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20New%20York%2C%20while%20high%20school%20graduates%20made%20%2440%2C000.%20Over%20the%20course%20of%20their%20careers%2C%20men%20and%20women%20with%20bachelor's%20degrees%20earn%20a%20median%20%24900%2C000%20and%20%24630%2C000%2C%20respectively%2C%20more%20than%20their%20counterparts%20who%20graduate%20from%20high%20school%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Social%20Security%20Administration.%20And%20white-collar%20bosses%20still%20want%20to%20hire%20college-educated%20workers.%20%26quot%3BWe've%20not%20seen%20an%20erosion%20from%20employers%20who%20suddenly%20can%20do%20without%20a%20four-year%20degree%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Kevin%20Kruger%2C%20the%20president%20and%20CEO%20of%20FirstGen%20Forward%2C%20an%20organization%20focused%20on%20helping%20first-generation%20college%20students.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAI%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20also%20isn't%20the%20college-killer%20some%20feared%20it%20to%20be%20when%20ChatGPT%20swept%20through%20campuses%20three%20years%20ago.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20think%20higher%20ed%20loses%20its%20value%2C%20but%20I%20do%20think%20it%20has%20to%20adapt%20to%20technology%20very%20rapidly%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Safinah%20Ali%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20educational%20communication%20at%20New%20York%20University's%20Steinhardt%20School.%20She%20sees%20meaningful%20uses%20for%20AI%20being%20taught%20across%20disciplines%20%E2%80%94%20not%20just%20in%20technical%20subjects%20like%20computer%20science%2C%20but%20in%20the%20humanities%20and%20arts.%20The%20younger%20students%20are%2C%20Ali%20says%2C%20the%20better%20they%20tend%20to%20be%20at%20embracing%20changes%20and%20new%20tools%20without%20worrying%20about%20how%20different%20the%20world%20will%20look%20in%20four%20years.%20Even%20Altman%20thinks%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-ai-workforce-future-jobs-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eyounger%20workers%20will%20be%20just%20fine%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20the%20older%20workers%20without%20a%20willingness%20to%20adapt%20that%20he%20fears%20will%20be%20hurt.%20%26quot%3BA%20lot%20is%20going%20to%20happen%20in%20six%20months%20to%2012%20months%2C%20so%20the%20notion%20of%20trying%20to%20predict%20exactly%20where%20we'll%20be%20in%20four%20years%20is%20nearly%20impossible%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Christine%20Cruzvergara%2C%20the%20chief%20education%20strategy%20officer%20at%20the%20early%20career%20site%20Handshake.%20That%20sounds%20scary%20to%20the%20seasoned%20worker%2C%20but%20for%20a%20college%20freshman%2C%20a%20year%20can%20feel%20like%20a%20lifetime.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20probably%20also%20an%20element%20of%20optimism%2C%20because%20they're%20just%20starting%20and%20they%20have%20four%20years%20ahead%20of%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20unlike%20young%20adults%20who%20enrolled%20in%20college%20at%20the%20outset%20of%20the%20Great%20Recession%2C%20today's%20freshmen%20may%20be%20sheltered%20from%20the%20worst%20of%20the%20AI%20storm.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20in%20the%20disruption%20phase%20at%20the%20moment%2C%26quot%3B%20Cruzvergara%20says.%20%26quot%3BMy%20guess%20would%20be%20in%20four%20years%2C%20we%20will%20have%20gotten%20out%20of%20some%20of%20that%20disruption%20phase%2C%20and%20we%20will%20be%20more%20in%20the%20calibration%20phase.%26quot%3B%20And%20as%20businesses%20calibrate%2C%20students%20have%20the%20relative%20freedom%20to%20experiment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20if%20a%20college%20goes%20too%20all%20in%20on%20AI%2C%20it%20risks%20not%20preparing%20students%20with%20the%20critical%20thinking%20and%20soft%20skills%20also%20necessary%20for%20successful%20careers.%20Recent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.media.mit.edu%2Fpublications%2Fyour-brain-on-chatgpt%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresearch%20from%20MIT%3C%2Fa%3E%20suggests%20that%20relying%20too%20heavily%20on%20ChatGPT%20can%20make%20people%20lazy%20and%20dependent%20on%20the%20tech.%20In%20the%20study%2C%20those%20who%20used%20ChatGPT%20to%20help%20write%20essays%20%26quot%3Bconsistently%20underperformed%20at%20neural%2C%20linguistic%2C%20and%20behavioral%20levels%26quot%3B%20compared%20with%20control%20groups.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theatlantic.com%2Fmagazine%2Farchive%2F2024%2F11%2Fthe-elite-college-students-who-cant-read-books%2F679945%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Atlantic%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported%20last%20year%20that%20students%20were%20arriving%20at%20elite%20colleges%20and%20struggling%20to%20read%20and%20parse%20novels.%20%26quot%3BEven%20for%20well-intentioned%20students%2C%20who%20don't%20want%20to%20cheat%2C%20it%20is%20impacting%20their%20ability%20to%20think%20and%20grow%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Annie%20Chechitelli%2C%20the%20chief%20product%20officer%20at%20Turnitin%2C%20which%20offers%20plagiarism%20and%20AI%20detection%20software.%20Because%20AI%20is%20changing%20so%20rapidly%2C%20she%20thinks%20colleges%20should%20focus%20more%20on%20developing%20broad-ranging%20soft%20skills%20rather%20than%20hyperfocusing%20on%20specific%20AI%20tools%20in%20a%20field.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20going%20to%20get%20back%20to%20generalists%2C%20because%20things%20are%20changing%20too%20quickly%2C%26quot%3B%20Chechitelli%20says.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20not%20a%20mental%20athlete%2C%20you're%20not%20going%20to%20be%20able%20to%20adjust.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20professors%20are%20opting%20to%20shun%20GenAI%20entirely%20and%20have%20students%20complete%20more%20tests%20and%20essay%20assignments%20in%20class%2C%20but%20there's%20a%20growing%20consensus%20that%20old-school%20assessments%20should%20be%20left%20in%20the%20past.%20In%20August%2C%20Grammarly%20released%20eight%20AI%20agents%20built%20on%20OpenAI%20and%20other%20large%20language%20models.%20The%20agents%20can%20take%20on%20tasks%20like%20evaluating%20a%20drafted%20essay%20against%20an%20assignment%20rubric%2C%20giving%20students%20suggestions%20for%20how%20to%20improve%20the%20paper%20and%20assigning%20a%20predictive%20grade.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGenerative%20AI%20has%20upended%20traditional%20essay%20assignments%2C%20and%20that%20calls%20for%20changing%20how%20students%20are%20tested%20and%20graded.%20%26quot%3BIf%20words%20are%20no%20longer%20a%20reflection%20of%20learning%2C%20you're%20going%20to%20have%20to%20assess%20learning%20differently%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Jenny%20Maxwell%2C%20the%20head%20of%20education%20at%20Grammarly.%20She%20sees%20the%20company's%20agents%20not%20as%20just%20ways%20to%20level%20the%20playing%20field%20in%20the%20five-paragraph%20essay%2C%20but%20as%20evidence%20that%20the%20way%20students%20are%20evaluated%20needs%20to%20change.%20It's%20less%20now%20about%20catching%20cheaters%20and%20more%20about%20finding%20new%20ways%20to%20show%20mastery%20of%20concepts.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20I'm%20actually%20hoping%20happens%20is%20the%20essay%20game%20is%20no%20longer%20the%20essay%20game%2C%26quot%3B%20Maxwell%20says.%20Maybe%2C%20she%20says%2C%20AI%20can%20push%20students%20to%20think%20deeper%20about%20concepts%2C%20so%20there's%20less%20expectation%20to%20regurgitate%20what%20they're%20taught%20in%20a%20standardized%20essay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProfessors%20are%20still%20figuring%20out%20the%20best%20ways%20to%20evaluate%20students%20while%20they%20use%20AI%2C%20and%20there's%20no%20consensus%20yet.%20Dennis%20Yi%20Tenen%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20English%20at%20Columbia%20University%2C%20is%20teaching%20a%20course%20called%20Writing%20AI%20this%20fall%2C%20focused%20on%20the%20ways%20AI%20tools%20are%20reshaping%20the%20writing%20process%20and%20their%20limitations%20to%20do%20so%2C%20and%20he%20says%20it%20quickly%20filled%20up%20with%20about%2080%20eager%20students%20who%20think%20there%20will%20be%20big%20returns%20on%20mastering%20AI.%20Teaching%20AI%20as%20a%20writing%20partner%20has%20already%20reshaped%20how%20he%20interacts%20with%20his%20students%2C%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BRather%20than%20performing%20expertise%20and%20lecturing%2C%20I'm%20much%20more%20brutally%20honest%2C%26quot%3B%20Yi%20Tenen%20says%2C%20explaining%20that%20he's%20become%20more%20candid%20about%20what%20we%20know%20and%20don't%20know%20about%20how%20AI%20works%20best.%20%26quot%3BWith%20a%20class%20on%20AI%20where%20stuff%20is%20so%20open-ended%20right%20now%2C%20nobody%20knows%20that%20answer.%20Let's%20experiment%20with%20this.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20colleges%20and%20professors%20still%20figuring%20out%20how%20to%20navigate%20AI%20and%20the%20cultural%20backlash%20to%20higher%20ed%2C%20there's%20room%20to%20reevaluate%20how%20students%20are%20assessed.%20Highly%20driven%20perfectionists%20arrive%20on%20campus%20with%20a%20history%20of%20straight%20A's%20and%20an%20avoidance%20of%20failure%2C%20and%20the%20hefty%20weight%20of%20tuition%20can%20discourage%20risk-taking%20%E2%80%94%20yet%20that's%20exactly%20what%20the%20protective%20bubble%20of%20a%20college%20experience%20should%20provide.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20not%20born%20with%20a%20specific%20set%20of%20talents%2C%20and%20we%20learn%20from%20failure%2C%26quot%3B%20Pasquerella%20says.%20%26quot%3BBut%20you%20have%20to%20have%20a%20curriculum%20that%20allows%20people%20to%20learn%20from%20failure%20and%20not%20kick%20them%20out%20if%20they%20fail%20their%20first%20few%20assignments.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOutside%20of%20the%20financial%20perks%2C%20college%20is%20a%20sandbox%20in%20which%20young%20people%20take%20baby%20steps%20to%20adulting.%20Part%20of%20the%20disconnect%20in%20the%20value%20of%20college%20comes%20from%20what%20young%20people%20actually%20get%20from%20four%20years%20spent%20eating%20processed%20foods%20and%20pledging%20sororities%20or%20fraternities.%20If%20you%20try%20to%20play%20a%20numbers%20game%20and%20break%20down%20the%20cost%2C%20plus%20interest%2C%20add%20the%20four%20years%20of%20your%20time%2C%20and%20then%20weigh%20that%20as%20an%20exact%20exchange%20for%20a%20specific%20job%20or%20salary%2C%20that%20misses%20some%20of%20the%20less%20tangible%20benefits.%20Colleges%20have%20to%20sell%20a%20bigger%20idea%20with%20their%20high%20ticket%20price.%20%26quot%3BYou%20need%20to%20make%20the%20value%20proposition%20more%20attractive%20in%20the%20immediacy%20for%20students%20to%20be%20willing%20to%20make%20the%20investment%2C%20because%20it%20looks%20so%20scary%20initially%2C%26quot%3B%20Mabel%20says.%20%26quot%3BThese%20are%20people%20that%20haven't%20lived%20much%20of%20their%20life%2C%20and%20they're%20hungry%20to%20have%20a%20crack%20at%20having%20some%20money%20in%20their%20pocket%20and%20being%20able%20to%20live%20their%20life%20as%20they%20want%20to.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConvincing%20some%20that%20the%20time%20and%20money%20invested%20in%20a%20degree%20won't%20be%20wasted%20is%20becoming%20a%20harder%20conversation%20for%20colleges%20in%20a%20world%20loudly%20criticizing%20higher%20ed.%20But%20coursework%20and%20campus%20life%20teach%20young%20people%20resilience%20and%20collaboration%20and%20expose%20them%20to%20new%20ideas%20and%20people.%20They%20spend%20those%20years%20learning%20to%20problem-solve%2C%20and%20the%20growth%20is%20about%20much%20more%20than%20the%20dozen%20or%20so%20hours%20a%20week%20spent%20in%20class.%20It's%20not%20the%20kind%20of%20skill%20or%20lesson%20that%20AI%20can%20undermine.%20The%20appeal%20of%20college%20isn't%20dead%3B%20it's%20just%20stuck%20in%20an%20awkward%20phase.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Famanda-hoover%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EAmanda%20Hoover%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%20covering%20the%20tech%20industry.%20She%20writes%20about%20the%20biggest%20tech%20companies%20and%20trends.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerica-colleges-identity-crisis-students-class-2029-ai-paradox-2025-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1756973462000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68b8a2d957d362d375e776ca%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerica-colleges-identity-crisis-students-class-2029-ai-paradox-2025-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Today's%20college%20freshmen%20face%20sky-high%20tuition%20and%20debt%2C%20shaky%20career%20paths%2C%20and%20mixed%20messaging%20on%20AI.%20Universities%20are%20scrambling%20to%20respond.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ahoover%40insider.com%20(Amanda%20Hoover)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A65%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerica-colleges-identity-crisis-students-class-2029-ai-paradox-2025-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22From%20Dining%20Out%20To%20Luxury%20Flights%2C